{"ID":270216, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"216\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs215.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs217.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 216<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">and be reconciled to His will;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> all is right. It will be but a short time before we shall all in like\n  manner be called: it may be the case with me as well as you. Some have supposed that Brother\n  Joseph could not die; but this is a mistake: it is true there have been times when I have had the\n  promise of my life<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> to accomplish such and such things, but, having now accomplished those things,\n  I have not at present any lease of my life, I am as liable to die as other men.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I can say in my heart, that I have not done anything against Ephraim Marks that I am sorry for,\n  and I would ask any of his companions if they have anything against him that they are sorry for, or\n  that they would not like to meet and answer for at the bar of God,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> if so, let it prove as a warning to\n  all to deal justly<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> before God, and with all mankind, then we shall be clear in the day of judgment.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">When we lose a near and dear friend, upon whom we have set our hearts,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> it should be a caution\n  unto us not to set our affections<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> too firmly upon others, knowing that they in like manner be taken\n  from us. Our affections should be placed upon God<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and His work, more intensely than upon our\n  fellow beings. (April 9, 1842.) DHC 4:587.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Synopsis of Remarks of the Prophet&mdash;Reproof of all Wickedness<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Joseph the Seer<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> arose in the power of God;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> reproved and rebuked wickedness before the\n  people, in the name of the Lord God. He wished to say a few words to suit the condition of the\n  general mass, and then said: I shall speak with authority of the Priesthood<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> in the name of the Lord\n  God,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> which shall prove a savor<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> of life unto life, or of death unto death.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> Notwithstanding this\n  congregation profess to be Saints,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> yet I stand in the midst of all [kinds of] characters and classes\n  of men. If you wish to go where God is,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> you must be like God,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> or possess the principles which\n  God possesses,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> for if we are not drawing towards God<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> in principle, we are going from Him and\n  drawing towards the devil. Yes, I am standing in the midst of all kinds of people.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Search your hearts,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and see if you are like God.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> I have searched mine, and feel to repent of\n  all my sins.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111219\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111219)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111219)\">2 Ne. 10:24<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115872\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115872)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115872)\">D&amp;C 122:9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111350\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111350)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111350)\">2 Ne. 33:11,15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111417\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111417)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111417)\">Jacob 6:9,13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112298\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112298)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112298)\">Alma 41:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112745\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112745)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112745)\">4 Ne. 1:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107985\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107985)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107985)\">Matt. 12:36<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111207\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111207)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111207)\">2 Ne. 9:46<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115235\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115235)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115235)\">D&amp;C 101:78<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106348\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106348)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106348)\">Deut. 32:46<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111608\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111608)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111608)\">Mosiah 12:29<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115809\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115809)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115809)\">D&amp;C 121:35<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116977\"><a href=\"javascrip